abstract: Nevada votes next and then South Carolina. But top Democrats vying for their party's presidential nomination are already looking ahead to the biggest prize on the primary calendar: Super Tuesday, the slate of contests when more than a dozen states go to the polls.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nevada votes next and then South Carolina. But top Democrats vying for their party's presidential nomination are already looking ahead to the biggest prize on the primary calendar: Super Tuesday, the slate of contests when more than a dozen states go to the polls.
headline_main: 2020 Hopefuls Eye Super Tuesday Even as 2 Other States Loom
headline_print_headline: 2020 Hopefuls Eye Super Tuesday Even as 2 Other States Loom

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Bernie Sanders, who bills himself as a champion of organized labor, found himself in an escalating feud with Nevada's Culinary Workers Union on Wednesday, 10 days before the state holds the party's third nominating contest.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Bernie Sanders, who bills himself as a champion of organized labor, found himself in an escalating feud with Nevada's Culinary Workers Union on Wednesday, 10 days before the state holds the party's third nominatin...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Democratic presidential candidate Bernie Sanders, who bills himself as a champion of organized labor, found himself in an escalating feud with Nevada's Culinary Workers Union on Wednesday, 10 days before the state holds the party's third nominating contest.
headline_main: Democrat Sanders, Nevada Union in Escalating Feud Ahead of State Nominating Contest
headline_print_headline: Democrat Sanders, Nevada Union in Escalating Feud Ahead of State Nominating Contest

abstract: Help wanted, and it’s named Ralph.
snippet: Help wanted, and it’s named Ralph.
lead_paragraph: Perhaps you think New Hampshire sent us a mixed message. After all, Bernie Sanders won but the moderates got more votes, and on Tuesday night three different candidates seemed to be giving victory speeches.

lead_paragraph: When senior government officials abuse their power by wielding law enforcement for private ends, whether to attack their enemies or protect their allies, they strike at the heart of constitutional democracy. They make a mockery of “equal justice under law,” the central animating principle of the American experiment and one that, in the main, Republican and Democratic administrations have striven to honor.

abstract: Nevada's most politically powerful union, the casino workers' Culinary Union, is so far staying quiet on whether it will endorse a candidate as the Democratic presidential race swings west, but Joe Biden isn't counting on the labor group's help.
snippet: Nevada's most politically powerful union, the casino workers' Culinary Union, is so far staying quiet on whether it will endorse a candidate as the Democratic presidential race swings west, but Joe Biden isn't counting on the labor group's help.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Nevada's most politically powerful union, the casino workers' Culinary Union, is so far staying quiet on whether it will endorse a candidate as the Democratic presidential race swings west, but Joe Biden isn't counting on the labor group's help.
headline_main: Nevada Union Might Not Endorse, but It Isn't Staying Quiet
